						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall, central shrine, Mahāliṅgasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 11: 982 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Varambusal-uḍaiyāṉ Chandrādichchaṉ Sattrukaṇḍaṉ of Veṇ-nāḍu donated 18 plates and one ladle for feeding the brāhmaṇas in the charity feeding house <hi rend="italic">(śālai)</hi> of the Tiruviḍaimarudu-uḍaiyār temple.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. V No. 714.</p>						

